ignificant liver cell damage.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.06824,0.11791,0.12756,0.12007,0.10383,0.089276,0.081723,0.072955,0.064205,0.061327,0.049545,0.043359],"unified_progress":[0.064163,0.091462,0.098696,0.10642,0.1047,0.09774,0.097354,0.084601,0.077071,0.072723,0.059482,0.045591]},{"section":5,"text":"Now, the serological tests: positive for HBsAg, IgM anti-HBc, and HBeAg.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.060033,0.10674,0.11253,0.10855,0.10127,0.093958,0.088406,0.081627,0.072996,0.066308,0.058788,0.048788],"unified_progress":[0.056095,0.089421,0.099361,0.10203,0.10569,0.099738,0.10233,0.087301,0.078835,0.070196,0.061345,0.047656]},{"section":6,"text":"Let me recall what each of these markers means.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32587,0.058194,0.058196,0.066401,0.065122,0.064832,0.05957,0.066176,0.064653,0.060545,0.062828,0.047611],"unified_progress":[0.21177,0.08376,0.069281,0.066515,0.076351,0.075617,0.087459,0.081124,0.075397,0.062142,0.056939,0.053643]},{"section":7,"text":"HBsAg is the surface antigen of hepatitis B, and its presence indicates an acute or chronic infection.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.061883,0.13184,0.062164,0.10362,0.1015,0.10167,0.091988,0.083079,0.075878,0.069868,0.062091,0.05442],"unified_progress":[0.075687,0.093747,0.06624,0.099649,0.097767,0.10391,0.094114,0.089407,0.083855,0.077694,0.065828,0.052102]},{"section":8,"text":"IgM anti-HBc is the IgM antibody to the core antigen, which is specific for acute hepatitis B infection because IgM class antibodies are produced during the initial infection.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042698,0.079825,0.091562,0.098555,0.10245,0.10089,0.10039,0.092316,0.083528,0.081068,0.06796,0.058767],"unified_progress":[0.051422,0.07057,0.089555,0.095424,0.10092,0.10393,0.10113,0.094988,0.088387,0.081291,0.068108,0.054273]},{